<paragraph id="533336B3E45AFFE0FF4967327EEDF896" blockId="52.[151,1436,1706,1947]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E45AFFE0FF4967327BFFF8CE" bold="true" box="[199,466,1814,1839]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
The species belongs in the 
<taxonomicName id="948C4D30E45AFFE0FC85673C7958F8CE" box="[779,885,1816,1839]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Beardius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncatus">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E45AFFE0FC85673C7958F8CE" box="[779,885,1816,1839]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">truncatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. The male can be separated from all other members of the genus by the combination of the following characters: tergite IX with median setae; and basal projection of the inferior volsella, parallel-sided, tapering towards apex, as long as the volsella.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
